</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":31,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Dalling was born about 1424. He had at least 1 son with Margaret. He died before 8 February 1473, in Laxfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, and was buried in Laxfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1424–Bef 8 February 1473":"umbes 1424–enne 8. veebruari 1473","–Female":"Surnud","1454–1535":"1454–1535","1424–1473":"1424–1473","1535":"1535","8 February 1472":"8. veebruar 1472","1424":"1424","Bef 8 February 1473":"enne 8. veebruari 1473","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","1473":"1473","Abt 1424":"umbes 1424","20 October 1471":"20. oktoober 1471","Laxfield, Suffolk, , England":"Laxfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Laxfield, Suffolk, England":"Laxfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1424–Bef 8 February 1473":"noin 1424–ennen vuotta 8. helmikuuta 1473","–Female":"Kuollut","1454–1535":"1454–1535","1424–1473":"1424–1473","1535":"1535","8 February 1472":"8. helmikuuta 1472","1424":"1424","Bef 8 February 1473